To test Avaliability Zones, run the above.  Then add "two", and update.  ELB should not require replacement.  Then remove both AZ's.  It should require replacement.  Then add an AZ again.  This should also require replacement.

Change the Scheme value to "internal' and update.  It should require replacement.

To test CrossZone, ConnectionSettings,  and AccessLogPolicy, add something like the following snippet to the template.
{code}
        "AccessLoggingPolicy" : {
          "EmitInterval" : "5",
          "Enabled" : "true",
          "S3BucketName" : "bucket",
          "S3BucketPrefix" : "buck"
        },
        "ConnectionSettings" : { "IdleTimeout" : "300" },
        "CrossZone" : "true",
{code}

Change the various parameters, and update the stack.  All can be seen with eulb-describe-lb-attributes <elb>.  Try removing parameters as well to make sure defaults are respected.  This should update the stack with no interruption.

We do not support ConnectionDrainingPolicy.

